721825f-a.folder: Murray Street & West Broadway, Manhattan, NY
721825f-a.text:
65 and 67 Murray Street, at and adjoining the N. W. corner of West Broadway. The corner building is also identified as No. 62-70
West Broadway.
December 10, 1914
Wurts Brothers

724365f-a.folder: West Broadway & Murray Street, Manhattan, NY
724365f-a.text:
West Broadway, east side, north from Murray Street. In the center is the Warren to Chambers Street frontage. The 6th Avenue
"El" line shown was removed in 1939.
December 10, 1914

724366f-a.folder: West Broadway & Murray Street, Manhattan, NY
724366f-a.text:
West Broadway, south from Murray Street. Note the new U.S. Post Office on the east side of West Broadway, south from Barclay to Vesey Streets.
November 6, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

724367f.folder: West Broadway & Murray Street, Manhattan, NY
724367f.text:
West Broadway, west side, from Murray to Warren Streets. The prominent structure bears No's. 62-70 West Broadway and 65 Murray Street.
December 10, 1914

Wurts Brothers
